instructions.step:
`thread_exit` is high-volume noise. Options:
(a) drop only `thread_exit` in Rust;
(b) drop in kernel for non-interesting exits;
(c) emit but filter in UI.
Prefer (a) or (b) — do not flood the log.

bug.severity:
Tauri `clear_injection_targets` only calls `set_injection_enabled(false)`. Kernel
`InjClearTargets()` exists but is never invoked via IOCTL. Target name list remains;
re-enabling injection reinjects old names. API name promises clear, behavior is disable.
